<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6038: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-14T17:00:00+08:00">March 14, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 14—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>249. American Consul General Tientsin informed me by telephone today that
                            Japanese have filed another protest with chairman of Hopei Provincial
                            Government, General Yu Hsueh-chung, against stationing of troops and
                            entrenchments in neighborhood of Tientsin and near Tangku as a violation
                            of the Boxer protocol.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>